rComments: Stinson is very approachable and always willing to help. Responds to emails quickly and is clear with instructions. His lectures were interesting as he incorporates personal travel stories to course content. Fun and engaging course, would definitely recommend to others.

Professor Stinson's class was interesting. You get what you put into it. I thought the readings and concepts were pretty basic, but the projects and tests helped to expand on them.  I would recommend taking it if your an anthropology major with no past experience in development studies or political science. The lectures were very informative.
Stinson was very helpful, almost immediately responds to e-mails
